'''{{free}}''' Host operating system <u>or</u>  VM can be booted into Live Mode, either by using:
 
* [[VM Live Mode]], <u>or</u> 
* [[Host Live Mode]].

This is accomplished by use of the [https://gitlab.com/whonix/grub-live <code>grub-live</code>] package.

= Troubleshooting =
For comparison see file <code>/etc/sudoers.d/whonix-xfce-desktop-config</code>.

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo --non-interactive /bin/lsblk --noheadings --all --raw --output RO
}}

{{CodeSelect|code=
sudo /bin/lsblk --all
}}

If you are still having issues you can [[Reporting_Bugs|report a bug]] with the information included from above.

